\section{Notation and Conventions}

throughout this document the metric tensor will be taken to be
\begin{align*}
  \eta_{\mu\nu} = \text{diag}(+1,-1,-1,-1)
\end{align*}
hence
\begin{align*}
  \pd_\mu \equiv \qty(\pd_t,\grad), \qquad V^\mu \equiv \qty(V^0,\vb{V})
\end{align*}
for any for vector with the standard convention that
\begin{align*}
  V_\mu = \eta_{\mu\nu}V^\nu = \qty(V^0,-\vb{V})
\end{align*}


